  "definitions": [
    {
      "definition": "A malignant germ cell neoplasm arising from the testis.  It is composed of primitive epithelial cells arranged in solid, papillary, and glandular configurations.  Most patients present with a testicular mass, which may be associated with pain.  More than half of the patients have metastatic disease at diagnosis.  The form of treatment following radical orchiectomy is stage dependent.",
      "type": "DEFINITION",
      "source": "NCI"
    }
  ],
